<item>
            <title>[CXF-2178] HTTP headers (and thus cookies) are not settable from client request context</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CXF-2178</link>
                <project id="12310511" key="CXF">CXF</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Code that attempts to set http headers for the client, such as:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            Map&amp;lt;String, List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;&amp;gt; headers &lt;br/&gt;
                = CastUtils.cast((Map)bp.getRequestContext().get(&quot;javax.xml.ws.http.request.headers&quot;));&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;            if (headers == null) &lt;/p&gt;
{
                headers = new HashMap&amp;lt;String, List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt;&amp;gt;();
                bp.getRequestContext().put(&quot;javax.xml.ws.http.request.headers&quot;, headers);
            }

&lt;p&gt;            List&amp;lt;String&amp;gt; cookies = Arrays.asList(new String[] &lt;/p&gt;
{&quot;a=a&quot;, &quot;b=b&quot;}
&lt;p&gt;);&lt;br/&gt;
            headers.put(&quot;Cookie&quot;, cookies);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;is not working with 2.2.   Worked fine with 2.1.3.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
